@startuml client_disconnect_sequence_diagram

participant ":LoggingClient" as Client
participant "main()" as Main
participant "mw::log::\nRuntime" as Runtime
participant "mw::log::\nSafeDatarouterBackend" as Backend
participant "mw::com::message_passing::\nReceiver" as Receiver

Client -> Main : (start)
activate Main

Main -> Runtime : GetRecorder()\nGetInstance()
note right of Runtime
  Creation of the Runtime
  Singleton that owns
  the Recorder.
end note

Runtime -> Backend : constructs
Backend -> Receiver : constructs
Receiver -> Receiver : launches\nReceiver thread

Main -> Runtime : Shutdown()
note right of Runtime
  Runtime::Shutdown() must be called
  before the return of main().
  After that no more calls to logging
  are allowed.
end note

Runtime -> Backend : deconstructs\n~Runtime()

Backend -> Receiver : Trigger stop source
Backend -> Receiver : join()

participant "mw::log::\nSharedLoggingData" as SLD

Backend -> SLD : Set Detached State
note right of SLD
  The detached state shall allow
  Datarouter to continue consuming
  all the messages remaining
  in shared memory without the need
  of synchronization with the client.
end note

Backend -> SLD : If Datarouter has discovered the file:\nunlink shared memory file
note right of SLD
  After Datarouter and the client have
  closed the file, the memory will be freed.
  The client only unlinks on shutdown if
  Datarouter has already discovered the
  file, i.e. Datarouter has sent at least one
  message to the client.
end note

Main --> Client : return
deactivate Main

note over Client, Main
  C++ static deinitialization
  phase begins after the
  return of main().
  At this point accessing
  any static state is unsafe.
  Thus the user must call
  Shutdown() before.
end note

@enduml
